<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-09-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-09-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="778" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d778">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hill</persName> to Lord
                                    <persName type="to">Pauncefote</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-09-19"><hi rend="italic">September 19,
                                    1900</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 1924.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your note, No. 265, of the 15th instant, by which you
                            transmit an expression of the great sorrow with which Her Majesty the
                            Queen has learnt the details of the terrible disaster at Galveston and
                            the assurance of her sincere sympathy with the unfortunate sufferers
                            from this calamity.</p>
                        <p>Your note has been communicated to the President, who charges me to
                            express his sincere appreciation of Her Majesty’s sympathetic
                            message.</p>
                        <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">David J. Hill</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>